      About this item

        This fits your .
      • Make sure this fits by entering your model number.
      • 3.5" External Hard Drive Enclosure -- Easily connects your 3.5/2.5 inch hard drive to a PC, laptop, and other device for massive data transfer and portable storage. It protects the hard disk from outside scratches and maximize the use of your 3.5"/2.5" HDD and SSD again, offers comprehensive protection for your valuable data.
      • 5Gbps with UASP Accelerated -- The maximum data transfer speed of the USB 3.0 interface is 5Gbps. Plus UASP accelerated transmission protocol, 70% Faster than than conventional USB 3.0 when connected to a computer that also supports UASP. Transfer 1GB files in seconds, saving up the loading time to do more. Backwards compatible with USB 2.0 and USB 1.1 ports.
      • Universal Compatibility -- Supports Windows 10/8.1/7, LINUX, Mac OS 8.0 and above systems. Specially designed for 3.5inch/2.5 inch SATA III/II/I HDD SSD up to 16TB. Compatible with WD, Seagate, Toshiba, Hitachi, Samsung, Crucial, SSD and HDD with sata port and so on. It can use on hard drive of PS4, PS4 Pro, PS3, Xbox One, Xbox 360, play more games stored in SATA drive, ideal to for entertaining and gaming
      • Easy Installation -- Plug and play with tool-free installation, no driver needed. Just push out the cover, plug in the drive, close the cover, plug the DC power adapter and go. Guaranteed with a stable and reliable energy supply for massive data transfer. Please click "Safely Remove Hardware" icon on your PC first then unplug it to avoid data loss when complete using.
      • Premium Design for Better Protection -- Build with premium ABS material with solid contruction to hold the hard drive firmly, the soften rubber strip provides anti-shock protection, the pre-set heat emission holes at the bottom for excellent heat dissipation. The Auto Sleep Mode helps to extend the lifespan of your hard drives.

      Product Description

      Great Portability, Get the Best Out of Your Both 3.5" and 2.5" Hard Drive

      Ideal for harnessing your 3.5 "/2.5"HDD and SSD hard drive as an external USB drive, it will provide you greater convenience of use and versatility of digital data storage. An ideal choice for digital lovers, movie lovers and business elites.

      5Gbps USB 3.0 with UASP, Faster and More Efficient

      The enclosure comes with the USB 3.0 connection enhanced with the UASP protocol, and significantly increases the data transfer rate, delivering up to 70% faster performance than conventional USB 3.0, quickly back up your photos, video, movie, games from your computer to the SATA Drive for storage.

      Shelter For Valuable Data

      Solid constructed external hard drive case, built with premium ABS material and soften rubber strip offers comprehensive protection for your SATA drive against scratches and drops, keeps the valuabe data in a safe place

      The pre-set heat emission holes at the bottom contributes for thermal dissipation for hard drive during working time

      Features S.M.A.R.T function and allows you to check the status of your HDD or SSD on computer easily.

      LED indicator lets you learn the working status of this External Hard Drive Enclosure easily.

      Made of durable ABS, solid and excellent heat dissipation, no cooling fan is needed for high-speed working.

      Read more

      Drive The Performance

      Easy assembly in seconds, tool-free

      Support Windows 10/8/7/XP, Linux, Mac OS, etc, driver-free

      Designed for 3.5" and 2.5 "hard drives (26mm max) up to 16TB

      Size: 194mm*117mm(W)*38mm(H)

      Intelligent Sleeping Mode for Power Saving

      The hard drive case will switch to low power consumption standby mode automatically if no data activity within 3 mins, but can be easily awakened by with data transmission

      Warm Reminder:

      • Always safely remove your disc before unplugging this product.
      • Please plug the power adapter when use for 3.5" hard drive.
      • Please make a partition for the new hard drive disk at the first use.

          How are ratings calculated?
          To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzes reviews to verify trustworthiness.

          Kelby Balson
          2.0 out of 5 stars Not great for streaming movies from as a NAS
          Reviewed in the United States on August 17, 2018
          Verified Purchase
          First of all this enclosure was very easy to use. I have this configured with a 3TB HDD and its plugged into my wifi router and configured as a NAS. The problem is that the "intelligent" sleep technology turns off the hard drive in the middle of a movie, killing the stream. There is no way to turn off the intelligent sleep, so my opinion is that there is no way to keep this hard drive enclosure in use as a NAS drive due to this.

          My advice to the manufacturer: Make the intelligent sleep function a setting that is optional.

          Livid J...
          4.0 out of 5 stars Almost perfect (for Xbox One)
          Reviewed in the United States on July 19, 2018
          Verified Purchase
          So after reading reviews of people using this for XB1 storage, I decided to give it a go with a spare 1TB HDD I had laying around to expand my XB1 space. Slapped the HD in there, plugged it in to the USB port on the back of the Xbox One S, hit the power button and it immediately recognized it and formatted it to work.

          One complication: the sleep mode function of the enclosure will stop the HD from running, and the Xbox does not have the capability to wake the HD up when you try to play a game installed on it. So you have to turn it off, than back on and wait for the XB1 to say the external storage is ready.

          It's not a complete buzzkill, but just a little annoyance. Wish there were a way to disable the sleep mode on the enclosure but otherwise it's a great, well built enclosure for a good price.

          Steve B.
          5.0 out of 5 stars Turned out to be a great enclosure
          Reviewed in the United States on April 1, 2018
          Verified Purchase
          I had some problems when I first got the enclosure because it didn't work with any of my three 1 TB drives (Seagate and Western Digital) and I originally gave it a one star and was planning on sending it back and I contacted the company and complained. However, I later found that the drives had not been inserted properly. I don't know if the alignment wasn't right but now it has been working with all the three drives now and I have been transferring data at very high speeds. I deleted the bad review and replaced with this one. When the drive gets hot, I open the easy open cover to vent the heat.           G.L.
          1.0 out of 5 stars The 'power light' that isn't.
          Reviewed in Canada on June 26, 2018
          Verified Purchase
          Update:

          I bought three of these enclosures. One of them has completely died. These enclosures are not reliable.

          Previously:

          This review is for the 50422, which I was sent instead of the 50423. (A scan of the manual is in the photo I've attached.)

          Very odd power management in this unit.

          When the unit is disconnected from Windows 7, the 'power light' goes off. But the unit is still on!

          If the computer is rebooted in this state, the unit will connect itself, and the 'power light' comes back on.

          So you'll have to remember to press the power ON/OFF button after disconnecting from Windows, even though the 'power light' is already OFF.

          If UGREEN had used a toggle switch for power ON/OFF, then this wouldn't be a problem because the switch would still be in the ON setting, until it is switched to OFF. Or, a second light could have been used as a power indicator.

          So, the blue light that comes on is NOT a power indicator. It is a connection indicator.

          What a poor design for both the light and the switch.

          For those interested, the ugreen.com web site has a download to turn off sleep mode for the 50422/50424. Go to DOWNLOADS/DRIVERS and then to User Manual/Upload.

          If the unit still goes into sleep mode, it might be because of a computer setting. If you have Windows 7, click Start (the 'pizza') and type in 'device manager' (without the quotes). [For Windows 10, just right-click the pizza.] Click on the Device Manager entry to run it, and near the bottom of the pop-up window, expand the Universal Serial Bus controllers section by clicking on the little arrow beside it on the left. Right-click on the first entry that ends with the word 'Hub' and then click on Properties. Now click on the Power Management tab. Uncheck the box for 'Allow the computer to turn off this device to save power.' Then click on OK. Use this procedure to change the setting for each Hub. Or if you just want to change the one that connects the UGREEN unit, you will have to experiment using trial and error. i.e. Change one Hub and see if the UGREEN stays on. If not, change the first Hub setting back, and then try the next Hub setting. When you find the correct Hub, you'll have to remember to always use the same USB port for the UGREEN unit.
